Class AeWaitableReplyReceiver

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
IAeReplyReceiver
public class AeWaitableReplyReceiver
extends AeReplyReceiverBase

Class used to handle the reply in a request response operation. This class's onFault and onMessage method notifies any waiting threads by calling notifyAll.

isWaitable

public boolean isWaitable()
This object is considered waitable if it its callback methods for receiving the message data, fault, or void signal haven't been invoked. This method should be used to determine if the object is in a waitable state before waiting on it. Failing to call this method (or testing the object's state through the aforementioned calls) risks waiting forever for a callback that will never be issued.
